{"primaryContentSections":[{"declarations":[{"platforms":["macOS"],"languages":["swift"],"tokens":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"func"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"addToggleRef"},{"text":"(","kind":"text"},{"kind":"externalParam","text":"notify"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"c:gobject.h@T@GToggleNotify","text":"GToggleNotify"},{"text":"?, ","kind":"text"},{"text":"data","kind":"externalParam"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"text":"gpointer","preciseIdentifier":"c:gtypes.h@T@gpointer","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"text":"? = nil)","kind":"text"}]}],"kind":"declarations"},{"kind":"content","content":[{"anchor":"discussion","text":"Discussion","level":2,"type":"heading"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"This functionality is intended for binding "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"object"},{"type":"text","text":" to a proxy"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"object managed by another memory manager. This is done with two","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"paired references: the strong reference added by"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_object_add_toggle_ref()"},{"type":"text","text":" and a reverse reference to the proxy"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"object which is either a strong reference or weak reference."}]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The setup is that when there are no other references to "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"object"},{"text":",","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"only a weak reference is held in the reverse direction from ","type":"text"},{"code":"object","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"to the proxy object, but when there are other references held to","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"code":"object","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":", a strong reference is held. The "},{"code":"notify","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" callback is called"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"when the reference from "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"object"},{"type":"text","text":" to the proxy object should be"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"“toggled” from strong to weak (","type":"text"},{"code":"is_last_ref","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" true) or weak to strong","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"(","type":"text"},{"code":"is_last_ref","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" false).","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Since a (normal) reference must be held to the object before","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"calling "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_object_add_toggle_ref()"},{"type":"text","text":", the initial state of the reverse"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"link is always strong.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Multiple toggle references may be added to the same gobject,"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"however if there are multiple toggle references to an object, none","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"of them will ever be notified until all but one are removed.  For"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"this reason, you should only ever use a toggle reference if there","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"is important state in the proxy object.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Note that if you unref the object on another thread, then "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"notify"},{"text":" might","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"still be invoked after "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_object_remove_toggle_ref()"},{"type":"text","text":", and the object argument"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"might be a dangling pointer. If the object is destroyed on other threads,"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"you must take care of that yourself."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"A "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_object_add_toggle_ref()"},{"text":" must be released with ","type":"text"},{"code":"g_object_remove_toggle_ref()","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":".","type":"text"}]}]}],"metadata":{"role":"symbol","title":"addToggleRef(notify:data:)","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"func"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"text":"addToggleRef","kind":"identifier"},{"text":"(","kind":"text"},{"kind":"externalParam","text":"notify"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"c:gobject.h@T@GToggleNotify","text":"GToggleNotify"},{"text":"?, ","kind":"text"},{"text":"data","kind":"externalParam"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"text":"gpointer","preciseIdentifier":"c:gtypes.h@T@gpointer","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"kind":"text","text":"?)"}],"roleHeading":"Instance Method","symbolKind":"method","externalID":"s:10GLibObject0B8ProtocolPAAE12addToggleRef6notify4datayySvSg_SpySo8_GObjectVGSgs5Int32VtXCSg_AGtF","modules":[{"name":"GLibObject"}],"extendedModule":"GLibObject"},"schemaVersion":{"major":0,"minor":3,"patch":0},"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject\/ObjectProtocol\/addToggleRef(notify:data:)"},"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/glibobject\/objectprotocol\/addtoggleref(notify:data:)"]}],"kind":"symbol","hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject","doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject\/ObjectProtocol"]]},"sections":[],"abstract":[{"text":"Increases the reference count of the object by one and sets a","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"callback to be called when all other references to the object are","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"dropped, or when this is already the last reference to the object","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"and another reference is established."}],"references":{"doc://GLibObject/documentation/GLibObject/ObjectProtocol/addToggleRef(notify:data:)":{"role":"symbol","title":"addToggleRef(notify:data:)","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"func"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"text":"addToggleRef","kind":"identifier"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"externalParam","text":"notify"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"c:gobject.h@T@GToggleNotify","text":"GToggleNotify"},{"text":"?, ","kind":"text"},{"text":"data","kind":"externalParam"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"gpointer","preciseIdentifier":"c:gtypes.h@T@gpointer"},{"text":"?)","kind":"text"}],"url":"\/documentation\/glibobject\/objectprotocol\/addtoggleref(notify:data:)","abstract":[{"text":"Increases the reference count of the object by one and sets a","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"callback to be called when all other references to the object are"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"dropped, or when this is already the last reference to the object","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"and another reference is established."}],"type":"topic","kind":"symbol","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject\/ObjectProtocol\/addToggleRef(notify:data:)"},"doc://GLibObject/documentation/GLibObject":{"abstract":[],"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject","title":"GLibObject","role":"collection","kind":"symbol","type":"topic","url":"\/documentation\/glibobject"},"doc://GLibObject/documentation/GLibObject/ObjectProtocol":{"type":"topic","role":"symbol","navigatorTitle":[{"text":"ObjectProtocol","kind":"identifier"}],"url":"\/documentation\/glibobject\/objectprotocol","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"protocol"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"identifier","text":"ObjectProtocol"}],"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"The base object type."}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject\/ObjectProtocol","title":"ObjectProtocol","kind":"symbol"}}}